projects.description:
Protocols     : RLC, MAC and RRC
Tools used   : Agilent-8960(E5515C), Anite SAT & Bugzilla.
Reference    : 3GPP (Release 7) TS 25.322(RLC), TS 25.321(MAC), TS 25.331(RRC), TS    34.123-1(Conformance test specification)
Platform      : Windows.
The project involves testing of Protocol stack with list of test cases provided by 3GPP organization. It also involves localizing the failures in Protocol stack, Bug tracking and bug reporting.
RLC and MAC are L2 protocols which are responsible for node to node to delivery of data within the UMTS networks.
	RLC can be operated in Transparent Mode, Unacknowledged Mode & Acknowledged Mode.
	RLC is responsible for Segmentation/concatenation of user data, Padding, Transfer of user data, Error Correction, In Sequence Delivery of Data, Flow Control, Sequence Number Checking, Protocol error detection & recovery, Ciphering & SDU discard.
	In RLC Layer to Layer communication is through Primitives and Peer to Peer communication is through PDU.
Roles and Responsibilities: 
•	Analysis, Testing and Bug Fixing of UMTS wireless protocol stack in Mobile Handset side. 
•	Providing Support for IOT (Inter Operability Testing), Conformance Testing, Field Testing.
                  Testing Mobile Protocol Stack Software with Anite Test Suite and Analyzing the    Problems reported during Testing with Anite Test Suite.
projects.title: Validating UE Protocol Stack using 3GPP Specifications.

projects.description:

 TS 34.123-1(Conformance test specification)

projects.description:
Coin Based Universal Mobile Battery Charger.
Softwares: Embedded C,MPLAB
Hardwares: Microcontroller(pic16F458), LCD, Driver(ULN 2003), Relay, Metal sensor,power supply,PCB, charging Devices.
Roles: Implementation of  circuits.And coding..
Description:  The user has to insert the coin and we assume that one particular coin is to be inserted only.  When the coin is inserted the sensor will read the  data and then the micro controller will give the option to the user as to which type of charger the user needs to use. The user can choose the same from the keypad provided.The   micro controller will then activate that charger using the relay unit and at this time it will display as charging and when that time is  completed,  it will disconnect the power. In the same way other cell phones can also be charged. Here we are assuming that one person can charge at a time.
projects.title: Coin Based Universal mobile  Battery Charger

projects.description:
RIP Protocol Conformance Testing.

Environment:  RIP enabled Cisco Router 2600 series and 2 Quagga Routers, Nemesis packet Injection Tool, Wire shark, TCL based Automation tool Expect.
 
Description: The Project gave a detailed understanding of RIP Protocol and its functioning. Testing was done using the well known industry standard UNH IOL's RIP Operations Test Suite. Nemesis Packet Injection Tool was used to send a RIP packet as payload to the RUT (Router under Test) and then the updates in the RUT's Routing Table was observed. The transmission of RIP updates were observed on both of RUT's interfaces with the help of Wire shark. Automation was availed with the help of TCL Expect for SSH and Telnet sessions for the testing
projects.title: RIP Protocol Conformance Testing.

projects.description:
Technology:   Internet of Things (IOT),cloud networks,MQTT protocols,
Tools:Raspberry pi, Sensors (Temperature, LDR, Motion),ADC,Comparator
Building a prototype of a Home Automation System, where you can control and monitor conditions of your home and various appliances using a Mobile App.
Description.
On the Raspberry pi micro controller board we are connecting the temperature sensor, light sensor and a motion sensor. Mainly the sensors are the analog sensor (light and temperature) are connected to the ADC and digital sensor are connected to gpio ports of the Raspberry pi. We are getting a value from that sensors through Raspberry pi and uploading to particular value in to cloud.
.In Raspberry pi there is no analog to digital converter so that we are using  PCF8591P. It is a single chip ,single supply low power 8 bit cmos data acquisition device  with 4 analog inputs 1 output and serial I2c  bus interface
PC or Mobile side we are connecting the pc or the android mobile app to access that data from the cloud. And this data can be monitored anywhere in the world through an internet enabled application.In this project is  used the MQTT protocol and programming language is python.


.
projects.title: Smart Home using Cloud Networks and Mobile Devices.

The Role of Virtual Reality Gamification in Rehabilitation:

Virtual Reality an Immersive technology that offers a simulated environment where users can interact with digital content in a three dimensional space. VR has the potential to enhance Patient engagement, Motivation, and Outcomes across various rehabilitation settings. 

Motor Rehabilitation: 

VR based Motor Rehabilitation programs focus on Improving Motor function, Coordination, and Movement accuracy in individuals with neurological conditions such as Stroke, Traumatic brain injury (TBI), and Multiple sclerosis (MS). 

Gross motor skills refer to larger movements involving Multiple Muscle groups like Walking or Jumping.

Fine motor skills involve more precise movements  like Buttoning a shirt or Picking up small objects.

Physiotherapy  focuses on improving both types of skills through exercises and activities tailored to each individual's needs and abilities.

Balance and Gait Training: 

Balance and gait impairments are common challenges in individuals with Neurological Disorders, Orthopedic injuries, and Aging related conditions. VR based balance training programs utilize interactive games and simulations to challenge and improve postural control, balance reactions, and gait patterns. These immersive experiences provide real time feedback and progression tracking, allowing therapists to customize interventions and monitor progress effectively.

Cognitive Rehabilitation: 

VR technology offers promising opportunities for cognitive rehabilitation in individuals with acquired Brain injuries, Neurodegenerative diseases and cognitive impairments. 

Cognitive training programs implemented through VR platforms target various cognitive domains such as Attention, Memory, Executive function, and Visuospatial skills. By engaging patients in stimulating cognitive tasks and challenges within virtual environments, therapists can promote cognitive retraining and functional independence.

VISHNUPRAKASH P 
OQULIX
